===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|drove}}, {{m|enm|drof}}, {{m|enm|draf}}, from {{inh|en|ang|drāf||action of driving; a driving out, expulsion; drove, herd, band; company, band; road along which cattle are driven}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*draibō||a drive, push, movement, drove}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*dʰreybʰ-||to drive, push}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*dʰer-||to support}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|drave}}, {{m|sco|dreef||drove, crowd}}, {{cog|nl|dreef||a walkway, wide road with trees, drove}}, {{cog|gmh|treip||a drove}}, {{cog|sv|drev||a drive, drove}}, {{cog|is|dreif||a scattering, distribution}}. More at {{l|en|drive}}.

